item.title: Need help with compileing
item.dc:creator: @hipritchard hipritchard
item.description:
@hipritchard wrote:

right click on compile and choose edit:
if ure using a nixscape source it will look like this

@echo off
COLOR 08
title The Scape Of Death Client
“E:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_05\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
“E:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_05\bin/java.exe” server
pause

well u wana change that to this

@echo off
COLOR 08
title put ure server name here Client
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_07\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
“C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_07\bin/java.exe” server
pause

if ure using a whitescape source u will see

@echo off
COLOR 08
title The Scape Of Death Client
“E:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_05\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
“E:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_05\bin/java.exe” server
pause

well change it to this

@echo off
COLOR 08
title put ure server name here Client
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_07\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
“C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_07\bin/java.exe” server
pause

if your using a cheezscape or testscape it will look like

@echo off
title CheezScape Compiler or instead of cheezscape it says testscape
javac *.java
pause

change it to this

@echo off
title CheezScape Compileror put testscape compiler depends wich ur usin
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_07\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
“C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.5.0_07\bin/java.exe” server
pause

hope i helped:)
